article.headline: Rutgers 82, St. Thomas Aquinas 41
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Rutgers' new head coach Fred Hill had his first win with the team as the Scarlet Knights defeated St. Thomas Aquinas 82-41 on Sunday afternoon. Sophomore forward J.R. Inman was the lead scorer for Rutgers, grabbing six rebounds and scoring a game-high 15 points. Sophomore forward Jason Griffin matched his career-high with 13 points on five-for-seven shooting from the field. Senior forward Adrian Hill and junior forward Ollie Bailey each had 10 points. It was a chance for Rutgers (1-1) to come back from its loss to Kansas State during its season-opener. "What we wanted was to come out and do what we do, and that's to defend, and rebound, and run, and play for a full 40 minutes. And I though that we did that very well against Kansas State and certainly I thought we did that today," Hill said. Willis Ketrell led St. Thomas Aquinas (0-2) with 14 points. The Scarlet Knights never trailed in the game. They put the game away with a 17-2 run to open the second half. They capped the run with an Inman three-point jumper that opened the Rutgers lead to 55-25 with 14:09 left to play. Rutgers dominated the St. Thomas Aquinas throughout. The Scarlet Knights shot 51.7 percent from the field, while the Spartans were held to 27.5 percent. When it came to rebounding, Rutgers had a 43-27 edge. The Scarlet Knights' next game is Tuesday, hosting Jackson State in the second round of the Chicago Challenge Invitational.
